#define STORE_UNALIGNED ( val,
dst   ) 
Value:
({                                                      \
        typeof(val) __val = (val);                      \
                                                        \
        CLASSERT(sizeof(val) == sizeof(*(dst)));        \
        memcpy(dst, &__val, sizeof(*(dst)));            \
})

Stores val at dst, where the latter is possibly unaligned.

Uses memcpy(). This macro is needed to avoid dependency of user level tools on the kernel headers.
